{
  "texts": [
    "Given the potentially vast input space of our collision detection algorithms, such as the 6-dimensional space for a robot with 6 degrees of freedom, the scalability of NSGA-II is an advantage.• Proven Track Record: The NSGA-II algorithm has been successfully applied in diverse fields, demonstrating its robustness and efficiency in handling complex optimization problems.",
    "For instance, Wang et al. [111] utilized NSGA-II for fault diagnosis in power systems, showcasing its capability to identify fault components by transforming the diagnosis problem into a multi-objective optimization problem.",
    "This application highlights NSGA-II's adaptability in managing the complexities inherent in power systems' fault diagnosis.",
    "Similarly, Dhanalakshmi et al. [112] implemented a modified version of NSGA-II to address the combined economic and emission dispatch problem, indicating its versatility in optimizing both economic and environmental objectives within power systems.",
    "Additionally, Fang et al. [113] demonstrated the efficacy of an improved NSGA-II algorithm in emergency management, emphasizing its strengths in optimizing emergency response strategies."
  ]
}